<subSubSection id="C67F67DFFA38C9AA510D7C0D9E027DF1" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="26EF2DC1A5EE2660B65DDD38F52952CC" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CAD5EFA9236563A5B04249C0FC5C6E78" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">General coloration black. Haltere black with base of stem yellow. Wing with heavily brown bands and marks as follows: a large triangular brown mark in base of cells R and M; a irregular quadrate brown mark at origin of Rs; an elliptic brown mark at midlength of CuA1; a small oval brown mark at tip of A; median band extending from R to the bend in distal section of CuA2; subapical band extending from anterior margin of wing, covering tip of R1 and R2, to tip of M2; Rs about three-fifths the length of R4+5, 4 times the length of r-m.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
