</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="310F31E80A778BDFCC6D504EDE729BDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="B52135D1202FD3618E2ED16059089F10" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8F593416D79E21D4B6D7039E5FCB9246" pageId="0" pageNumber="87">
The determined specimen of this species collected from Zhejiang was identified by Alexander in 1939, but was not officially published to record. We re-determined it during the study and now record this species from Zhejiang for the first time. For descriptions and illustrations of this species, see 
<bibRefCitation id="4D4DAE62F4F2F186DC5E89EFFBB9C51D" author="Alexander, CP" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="140 - 143" refId="B3" refString="Alexander, CP, 1937. New species of Ptychopteridae (Diptera). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society 32: 140 - 143" title="New species of Ptychopteridae (Diptera)." volume="32" year="1937">Alexander (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="4556E1E461FA0CD5DE66160B0924BE6D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/01650429309361504" author="Krzeminski, W" journalOrPublisher="Aquatic Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="87" pagination="65 - 87" refId="B10" refString="Krzeminski, W, Zwick, P, 1993. New and little known Ptychopteridae (Diptera) from the Palaearctic region. Aquatic Insects 15: 65 - 87, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/01650429309361504" title="New and little known Ptychopteridae (Diptera) from the Palaearctic region." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/01650429309361504" volume="15" year="1993">Krzeminski and Zwick (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
